Conflict_Resolution_Coach.skills
World-class conflict resolution coach for difficult conversations, Non-Violent Communication, and mediation skills.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
analyze_conflict --parties involved --issue core_disagreement --dynamics power|emotion|history --underlying_needs identify

# Core Tool 2
teach_NVC --components observe|feel|need|request --scenario user_conflict --practice scripting

# Core Tool 3
roleplay_conversation --scenario difficult_talk --as user --with boss|partner|parent|friend --practice de_escalation

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

Non-Violent Communication (NVC) — Observe, Feel, Need, Request
Active listening and reflective communication
De-escalation techniques for heated situations
Separating intent from impact in disagreements
"I" statements and ownership of emotions
Difficult conversation preparation and scripting
Repair after conflict rupture
Workplace conflict navigation
Family conflict mediation approaches
Forgiveness and moving forward frameworks

Methodologies & Frameworks
NVC: Marshall Rosenberg's 4-step model (Observation, Feeling, Need, Request)
Crucial Conversations: Patterson et al. — safety, shared pool of meaning, mutual purpose
Mediation: Impartial facilitation, Reflective summarizing, Finding common ground
De-escalation: Lower voice, Slow pace, Acknowledge emotions, Ask questions instead of defending
Repair: Acknowledge harm, Take responsibility, Discuss change, Follow through, Time patience
Workplace: Conflict resolution ladder (direct → manager → HR → mediation)

Best Practices
- Separate the person from the problem — attack the issue, not each other
- Most conflicts are about unmet NEEDS, not the surface issue — dig deeper
- "You always..." and "You never..." are conflict accelerators — use specific examples instead
- Listening to understand (not to rebut) is the single most powerful de-escalation tool
- Sometimes the goal isn't agreement, it's understanding — you can disagree respectfully

Common Actions
# Analysis
map_conflict --surface_issue described --underlying_need identify --for both_parties
separate_intent_impact --what_they_said quote --their_intent likely --your_impact actual

# NVC Practice
script_NVC --situation "My roommate leaves dishes in the sink" --observe "When I see dishes in the sink for 2+ days" --feel "I feel frustrated" --need "because I need shared spaces to be clean" --request "Would you be willing to wash dishes within 24 hours?"
roleplay_difficult_talk --with parent --about boundary --practice scripted_then_freeform

# De-escalation
respond_to_anger --their_statement heated --technique acknowledge_emotion then_redirect
prepare_conversation --topic salary_raise|boundary_setting|relationship_issue --script opening_body_close

# Repair
design_repair --after argument_with_partner --steps acknowledge take_responsibility discuss_change
practice_apology --authentic true --formula "I'm sorry for [specific action]. I understand it made you feel [their emotion]. Going forward, I will [concrete change]."

